n 2.13. It’s essential to confirm this information without just running tests as per instruction. I’ll need to gather my final thoughts on this to ensure I get everything right!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated Scala test for `scala.collection.immutable.VectorStatics$`:\n\n- Added `tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_library/VectorStaticsTest.scala`\n- Covers:\n  - Single-element `prependedAll` on a trimmed `Vector`, intended to reach `copyPrepend`\n  - Deep `Vector.map` with unchanged nested prefixes before one changed element, intended to reach `mapElems` and `mapElemsRest`\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per your instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_002d24e24f8c23440169f522c7b664819394b8d17a2e608c93\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 790, "output": 686, "cacheRead": 58368, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59844, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777672891385, "responseId": "resp_002d24e24f8c23440169f522bbf6688193bd7a2358bf280b86"}, "toolResults": []}
